author: costin
msg: - Added per/Handler notes. Notes are a faster form of attributes ( indexed array access
instead of hashtable lookup - the Hashtable lookup is outside of critical path )
- in servletWrapper, when we set the servlet class name we reset the servlet class and
make it un-initialized. It's not a common operation ( most wrappers are created and the
class never change), but if somebody change the class we need to deal with that.
- Jsp handling - if a servletClassName is known we will use it, even if path!=null.
